rences exist between the provinces an attempt has been made to avoid specific to Ontario The appropriate provincial code can be obtained from electrical inspection offices of your provincial power In Ontario it's Ontario The Ontario Hydro book isn't overly It's about C and includes mailed I hear that these standards are somewhat easier to read than the equivalent NEC Don't bother asking in Quebec DIY wiring is banned throughout the Subject Can I do my own wiring Extra pointers In most places homeowners are allowed to do their own In some they're Check with your local electrical Most places won't permit you to do wiring on other's homes for money without a Nor are you permitted to do wiring in commercial Multiple dwellings eg duplexes are usually considered semi commercial or commercial However many jurisdictions will permit you to work on semi commercial wiring if you're supervised by a licensed electrician if you can find one willing to If you do your own wiring an important point Do it NEAT and WELL What you really want to aim for is a better job than an electrician will After all it's your own home and it's you or your family that might get killed if you make a An electrician has time pressures has the skills and knows the tricks of the trade to do a fast safe In this FAQ we've consciously given a few recommendations that are in excess of code because we feel that it's reasonable and will impress the The inspector will know that you're an You have to earn his The best way of doing this is to spend your time doing as neat a job as Don't cut Exceed Otherwise the inspector may get extremely picky and fault you on the slightest Don't try to hide anything from the Use the proper Ie don't use a bread knife to strip wires or twist wires with your The inspector won't like it and the results won't be that And it takes And you're more likely to stick a hunk of wire through your hand that Don't handle house wire when it's very cold eg below or Thermoplastic house wire parti